Subject: Neon?
Date:    Wednesday, 03 May 1995 20:43:07 
From:    plucas@vt.edu (Perry Lucas)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

How do you make a Neon light?  I have been playing around with
FOG, Bright, and Haze, but to little avail. 

Also here is a request for an update.

Barndoors - For those that do not know, shutters that attach to a
light so that you can control where the light falls more accurately.

                _____________
                |\         /|
                | \       / |
                |  \_____/  |
                |   |___|   |
                |  /     \  |
                | /       \ |
                |/_________\|

Okay, so I am not the best ascii artist, but the doors allow you to direct
the light.  For this to work, the light lines feature would have to be extended
and, a falloff circle would have to be created, and some other features to
let you know where the light is going.  (Like 3d studio)

--Perry


