  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

On Fri, 5 May 1995, Anime a day... wrote:
> >   What is the procedure to ask for a change for a DIGEST IML?
> 
>  There was a lot of talk about doing one in Amiga Guide format.  BUt then 
> PC users wanted to view it also... there are programs that can take an 
> ascii file and make good Amiga Guides out it with a little effort.. 
> Amazing Computing had a review about such a program...  anyway.. an ascii 
> file could work for both worlds, but who is willing to do it??? Who has 
> the time???

A digest format is something done BEFORE the messages get to your system. 
Instead of getting dozens of IML messages mixed in with all your other
mail, you get ONE big file once a day with all the messages in it. Much
more convienent for many people.  Most mailing list software supports this
automaticly, but I do not think the current software in 'standard' due to
all the bouncing undeliverable mail messages that happen now and then and
the problems with dual replies, ect. 

