     Oh, yes, the Forms editor.
     
     Well, it's nice.
     
     It's not as useful as the deformation tool (is supposed to be), but 
     the Forms editor did produce some nice things. I'm pretty sure that if 
     you really needed to use it, you could use one of your 10 machines :) 
     and just run Forms on that machine and port your objects over the 
     Ethernet 100Mbps wiring between the Cray and the Indigo Reality Engine 
