  You'll find that there are many fewer 32 bit C compilers for the PC 
than the Amiga, so many of the texture support is more difficult.  Amiga 
users also tend to be more of a roll-your-own group.  Don't fret, though, 
as the Imagine/Turbo-Silver platform has only been out on the PC one 
fifth the time as it has the Amiga.

ObImBit: A vortex type object looks great with a wide angle lense, trick 
is to make it look like a vortex.  Use ADPro to "Twirl" almost any image 
and map it X&Z flat onto the vortex object.

Mr.Kelly Petlig <kpetlig@halcyon.com>
