Hi all,

wouldn't it be a lot easier if you could just specify the maximum angle you
would like to have in your object, to reduce the point/edge/face count?
This way you also get rid of a lot of inline vertices forming a simple straight
line.
And it would also be neat if you could convert a spline from the spline editor
to a path for use in stage or extrusion in detail.
You can make an outline of edges and points in spline though, for use in the
detail editor with spin or sweep or something. Just make sure the shape is c
closed and don't add any faces.

