@node IML-464 " MSG-464  Subject: Re: Quickies (snow)
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Quickies (snow)
Date:    Wednesday, 24 May 1995 01:44:12 
From:    gregory denby <gdenby@elgreco.helios.nd.edu>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


I wrote some stuff about making quick snow showers, and Marty (Keitel)
replied "Why not use the particle effectwith the rain option..."

I've got to admit that after my first few tries with particle, and
was unable to figure just what was going to happen with the FX, I
decided to form shapes by hand.  That way I could be assured of not
having particles flying out of walls or bouncing of of invisible
coordinates. 

Just recently I've been working with the FX a lot more, and I suppose
I'll get a better grasp of how they work.  For now it is still easier
to make a shape out of fractured faces, and sweep 'em around a corner.

Greg Denby
gdenby@darwin.cc.nd.edu

