I looked at Ethernet for some time, but on the amiga it is costly and not 
very strongly supported (IBM already has a card) so for my pentium to 
amiga data I'm going to use a ZIP drive. They are had to find right now 
due to populatity, but for $200 you get a removable SCSI drive, and each 
$15-$20 disk holds 100Megs.  It's SCSI, it's external... all I have to do 
is find a SCSI 50 ribbon --> scsi 25pin cable for the IBM .. figure out a 
mountlist for the amiga side... (useing crossdos) and... bingo copy 100 
megs per disk...(about 1 meg per sec) re-hook it to the amiga.. all done.


