@node IML-558 " MSG-558  Subject: Re: Editor color preferences
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Editor color preferences
Date:    Sunday, 28 May 1995 00:19:42 
From:    rbyrne@3dform.edex.edu.au (Robert Byrne)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Hello Dennis, on May 26 you wrote:

> Which colors are people using for the editor colors, or is everyone using
> the defaults?

I've been using these since V2.0

BGRD  888     # background color
FGRD  000     # edge color
REQC  e92     # requester & gadgets color (bounding box & drag points)
BVLB  fc7     # bright bevel color (points & group lines)
BVLD  b62     # dark bevel color (selected objects edges & points)
GRID  999     # grid color
PICK  66f     # picked edge color
PPNT  f66     # picked point color
SPCK  94f     # selected picked edge (was c6f)
SPPT  0b0     # selected picked point (was ff6)
BWLC  fff     # line color in "B & W Wire/Shade"
COLC  fff     # line color in "Color Shade"
STAR  888     # star color in "Trace" and "Scanline"
COL0  000     # "color 0" RGB value for stills


-- Bob

  : Robert (Bob) Byrne : rbyrne@3dform.edex.edu.au :
  :   Amiga  A3000/25  :  Ballina, NSW  Australia  :


