  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  



On Wed, 24 May 1995, Robert Byrne wrote:

> If Imagine had an Arexx interface the ASCII scripts that Vista produces for
> the camera could come in real handy. These scripts contain the map
> coordinates, pitch, roll, yaw etc. You could render an aircraft or vehicle
> on a black background to follow the Vista camera movements and composite it
> onto the Vista landscape. 
> 
Yes. And even without Arexx you could always load the Vista script into 
some text editor and write down the coordinates and values by hand (after 
first finding out how the parameters are organized in vista scripts) and 
use them in the imagine script. But: Unfortunately this does not help, if 
you want to place objects on the ground. Because then they would have to be 
sometimes partially or totally covered by the hills in the landscape.

Marty



