I believe the default Imagine background color is 5,5,5, and on my 
screen, it makes text and numbers very hard to read. I lightened it up 
to 6,6,6 and left everything else the same.

Tip: in Preferences, you (1) click on a parameter to edit, then (2) 
enter values in the label and value fields. You're told that the color 
sliders and color swatch are there only to assist you visually. I don't 
remember, however, if the 3.0 docs ever got around to mentioning that if 
you CLICK ON THE COLOR SWATCH, the slider numbers will be automagically 
copied into the value field -- no manual typing required.


